## 5.6 Cut-Off Times
Strict cut-off times are enforced along the route to protect course marshal welfare and ensure runner safety. Endurancelife events are running challenges; they are not walking events, and there are no extended cut-offs at the final finish line.

*Critical Timing Rule:* **All cut-off times are based on the time you depart the checkpoint, not when you arrive.** The pace requirements between checkpoints are not always uniform, so plan carefully. If you do not clear a checkpoint by the specified cut-off time, you must stop, surrender your bib to the marshal, and await official event transport. You will be classified as a DNF.

